This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of "cs.CL" (Computation and Language) as it deals with unsupervised learning of syntactic structure. It could also belong to "cs.LG" (Machine Learning) and "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence) as it proposes a novel generative model. Additionally, it could be relevant to "cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it uses an invertible neural network. Finally, it could be relevant to "cs.CV" (Computer Vision) as it deals with continuous word representations.
